# Gradient Descent — Multivariable Linear Regression

Implementation of multivariable linear regression with gradient descent from scratch using NumPy.

## What it does
- Generates synthetic data with 10 examples and 3 features
- Applies Z-score feature scaling
- Runs gradient descent for 1000 iterations
- Prints cost and weights every 100 iterations

## Concepts covered
- Vectorized forward pass with matrix multiplication
- MSE cost function
- Gradient descent weight update
- Feature scaling (standardization)

## Requirements
```bash
pip install numpy
```

## Usage
```bash
python gradient_descent_multivariable.py
```